8 PROPOSED COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to schools; requiring teaching of
human growth and development curriculum; specifying
10 curriculum requirements; requiring school districts
to offer human growth and development curriculum;
11 allowing district to choose how to incorporate
certain instruction; requiring certain instruction
12 for graduation; requiring integration of certain
instruction with health or science education;
13 requiring opt-in permission form be provided to
parents and legal guardians; providing for opt-in
14 permission form; mandating the human growth and
development curriculum be incorporated in the state
15 academic content standards; directing the State
Department of Education to develop certain guidelines
16 and resources for schools and teachers; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
17
18
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 11-203 of Title 70, unless there
23 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 13060 Page 1
1 A. Human growth and development curriculum shall be taught in
2 the public schools of this state. Human growth and development
3 education shall include, but is not limited to:
4 1. Human biology related to pregnancy;
5 2. Human development inside of a womb;
6 3. A high-definition ultrasound video, at least three (3)
7 minutes in duration, showing the development of the fetus in a
8 biological woman; and
9 4. A high-quality, computer-generated rendering or animation
10 showing the process of fetal development, highlighting significant
11 markers in cell growth and organ development until birth.
12 B. School districts shall provide the curriculum described in
13 subsection A of this section to students if the student's parent or
14 legal guardian complete an opt-in permission form. Schools may
15 incorporate the curriculum into an existing course or courses or
16 develop curriculum for a separate course. Schools shall provide
17 parents and legal guardians an opt-in permission form to authorize
18 their child be taught the curriculum described in subsection A of
19 this section two (2) weeks prior to the date the curriculum is to be
20 taught. The opt-in permission shall be on a form prescribed by the
21 State Board of Education and retained by the school district.
22 C. In order to graduate from a public high school accredited by
23 the State Board of Education with a standard diploma, students in
24 grades nine through twelve shall receive human growth and
Req. No. 13060 Page 2
1 deve lopment instruction as described in subsection A of this section
2 unless the student's parent or legal guardian did not complete an
3 opt-in permission form as provided for in subsection B of this
4 section or the student has an Individualized Education Program (IEP)
5 for a significant cognitive disability. Such instruction shall be
6 integrated into health or science education and shall be
7 incorporated into the state academic content standards adopted by
8 the State Board of Education pursuant to Section 11-103.6 of Title
9 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
